        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2015-09-01 02:31:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nFrank the checkpatch changes should detect if any patches coming in are using the old typedefs. I do agree this patch is already large so combining both patches would not be such a big deal. I will push the second patch hard to get it merged especially since only bug fixes are only going which lessens chances of collisions.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "e5c5df374f3dcb4047d259917317d27116c84571",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-09-01 08:02:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nFrank, the whole point of making two patches was to allow in-flight patches to land without disrupting development completely.  Once the first patch lands then we can wait a week or so until any in-light patches land and/or rebase and catch warnings, and then the second patch can be refreshed and landed.  Otherwise, this patch will need to be refreshed several times itself if other patches slip in that are adding any typedef usage.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
